str = pointer to a character
*str = value at the pointer contained in str
&str = address of the variable str

null-terminated string "hello" where the first character 'h' at address 0x12344567
*str == character 'h'
&str = address of the variable str: example 0x87492834

str = 0x12344567
*str = 'h'
&str = 0x87492834
str[0] = 0x12344567
str[1] = 0x12344571
